It’s Melanoma Monday!! When was the last time you’ve had your moles checked? In the last month alone, I’ve found 8 melanomas! That means 8 lives saved! 🙌🙌

In honor of Melanoma Awareness Month it’s important to educate!
 .
Melanoma is the most deadly form of skin cancer because if it isn’t detected early, it can spread to other organs! Yes, a mole or a freckle on your skin can spread internally!!!! 💡 The more you know! 
.
9,500 people per day in the US develop skin cancer. 
.
2 people die every hour from melanoma!
. 
Schedule your Full Body Skin exam today!! #getnaked

Don’t forget your sunscreen this weekend! ☀️🧴
Did you know that 80% of sun damage occurs before age 18! I always recommend a mineral based sunscreen with zinc oxide with a minimum SPF 30! 
.
Babies can start using sunscreen after 6 months. Protect that super soft baby skin. Light weight long sleeve shirts and a broad rim hat are the best! 
.
My favorite sunscreens for kids are baby Bum mineral face stick and lotion , blue lizard mineral for kids or Elta MD face stick.
For Adults: Elta MD UV Sport or UV AOX Mist
